          Oh and for those who think Ronaldo isn't an issue, take away his 7 league penalties this season (6 scored) and he has needed 9.1666 shots per goal. But he also creates chances you say? He has created an average of just 0.85 per game. The only word for that is pathetic. This is supposed to be the best player in the world. Yes, football is about more than the countable stats and Ronaldo just being on the pitch alters opposition team tactics, but he is given FAR too much responsibility to produce that little. I would like to see a front 3 of Vazquez, Morata and Asensio play a run of games against lesser opposition. Morata's shots per goals ratio is an astonishing 4.625 (5.5 is world class); Vazquez makes 1.36 key passes per game; Asensio's creativity is similar to Ronaldo (0.86 chances/game) while scoring a goal every 5 shots. Give the penalty taking duties to Morata, he hasn't missed in his professional career. The issues are the front 3 and Zidane's tactics, not the midfield 3 imo.

          Not sure why people want Kroos out of the midfield when he is the best CM in the world at dictating play and that is exactly why Real bought him. That is also ignoring the fact he has created the 3rd most chances in La Liga this season among midfielders (4th overall) despite playing the deepest of the 3 (Viera for Las Palmas & P.Leon of Eibar are 1 & 2). It is not a fluke he has a pass success rate of 92% despite making the 5th most total accurate passes and having an average pass length of 20m. Nobody has made more successful passes at the same (or higher) percentage with as long (or longer) an average pass length. He and Casemiro are irreplaceable for the jobs they do. Modric (1.333 chances per game) also creates more than Isco (1.2 chances per game) & is more consistent than James. If there is an issue with defensive duties then that is Zidane's fault for not drumming it into them where they have to be and when. Kroos is not a natural defender and shouldn't actually be defending!

        • [ - ] SteveHyland - member since 03-Nov-12

          @CirdomAkul- Real Madrid are the most efficient team in the league at creating chances per percentage of possession (346 chances created from 54% possession on average compared to Barcelona's 313 from 60% and Atletico's 252 from 50%) and Kroos has 58 of those (the most in the team by 30 chances over Carvajal). In most teams, you have other players who can compensate for defensive weaknesses so the midfield as a whole isn't weak but in Madrid, largely because Zidane doesn't have a clue defensively, you don't.
